InitExtension Failed" when accessing SBM
If an AppScript is using "now" to set a field value, the result may not be saved correctly and will display to the user as "Error".

For example, if the AppScript looks like this:
Call Shell.Item.SetFieldValue("Close Date", now)
 
The value will be saved to the database with a value of:  "1
899-12-26 00:00:00.000"
Also, when users look at the State form, the value of the field displays as the word "Error" instead of a date.
